Polymetal, Norilsk Nickel, Lukoil, VTB: Russian Equity Preview

-- B y   S c o t t   R o s e
-- 
2011-10-24T01:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-24/polymetal-norilsk-nickel-lukoil-vtb-russian-equity-preview.html
The following companies may be
active in Russian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and
share prices are from the previous close.  The 30-stock Micex Index rose 2 percent to 1,447.01. The
dollar-denominated RTS Index advanced 2.4 percent to 1,456.73.  OAO Polymetal (PMTL RX): The Russian gold and silver
producer may announce the terms for shareholders to swap their
stakes into stock in U.K.-based Polymetal International Plc. The
shares fell for the first day in six, losing 0.1 percent to
498.50 rubles.  OAO GMK Norilsk Nickel (GMKN RX): The world’s largest
nickel producer may report third-quarter production results.
Norilsk’s shares dropped 1.2 percent to 6,570.00 rubles.  OAO Lukoil (LKOH RX):  Russia ’s second-biggest oil producer
plans to comply with requirements sought by the Bulgarian
government relating to its Neftochim Burgas refinery by May, RIA
Novosti reported, citing Lukoil vice president Vadim Vorobyov.
The shares rose 2.4 percent to 1,743.00 rubles.  VTB Group (VTBR RX): The country’s second-biggest bank said
Oct. 21 that it sold 225 million Swiss francs ($255 million) in
debt due in 2015 to yield 5 percent. VTB’s shares rose 4
percent, the most in two weeks, to 6.775 kopeks.  To contact the reporter on this story:
